data.title: WSFS CARES Foundation donates $50,000 grant to address family homelessness in Delaware, partnering with Social Finance.
data.description: The WSFS CARES Foundation, affiliated with WSFS Financial Corporation (Nasdaq: WSFS), has revealed a $50,000 donation to Social Finance, Inc. data.title: Chewy, a pet supply leader, to acquire SmartEquine from Covetrus, expanding in equine health. SmartEquine offers subscription-based supplements.
data.description: A leading pet company, Chewy, Inc. (NYSE: CHWY) has confirmed the acquisition of SmartPak Equine, LLC (formerly SmartPak), a top U.S. provider of equine health products, from Covetrus, Inc. The deal includes SmartEquine's renowned subscription-based supplement programs, personalized nutrition plans, and extensive tack offerings. SmartPak Equine, rebranded in July 2025, is well-known for its high-quality equine products. This acquisition marks a significant move for Chewy in expanding its reach in the pet industry.

data.title: JPMorgan has tokenized private equity fund for wealthy clients, marking key milestone in digitizing investments.
data.description: JPMorgan Chase & Co. (NYSE: JPM) has recently tokenized a private-equity fund using its blockchain platform for affluent clients. This move signifies a significant advancement in the company's endeavor to digitize alternative investments. The tokenized fund is currently accessible to specific private-bank clients with plans for a wider launch in the coming year on JPMorgan's Kinexys Fund Flow platform. By converting fund ownership into digital tokens managed on JPMorgan's private blockchain, the system facilitates easier transfers and settlement processes. This initiative is part of JPMorgan's broader strategy to extend blockchain-based opportunities for alternative assets such as private credit, real estate, and hedge funds. The objective behind this approach is to enhance the tradability and management of typically illiquid investment vehicles for eligible investors. The trend of tokenization is gaining momentum in the financial sector as U.S. financial institutions ramp up their blockchain integration efforts, partly fueled by recent governmental actions. For more details, please refer to the complete article on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Fed Chair Powell resists December rate cut, but traders still expect a move. Market odds show 69-74% chance of 25-basis-point cut by Dec 10, as suggested by Powell's pause in policy shift. Fed faces division on inflation and labor market risks.
data.description: Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell pushed back against market expectations for a December rate cut, citing the need to proceed cautiously in uncertain times. Despite Powell's remarks, investors are still predicting a move by the end of the year. The market-implied odds of a December cut dipped slightly after Powell's comments but are still high. Traders currently assign a 69% chance of a 25-basis-point cut at the December 10 meeting, while a CFTC-regulated prediction market places those odds at 74%. Powell emphasized that a further rate reduction in December is not guaranteed, as the Federal Open Market Committee is divided on how to proceed due to varying perceptions of risks to inflation and the labor market. Powell's comments came after the Fed's decision to cut rates by 25 basis points to 3.75%-4.00%.

data.title: Google's stock rally hits 63% in 4 months with shares at $286, analyst say far from over. Price targets raised to $330 and $335 by Goldman Sachs and Bank of America.
data.description: Alphabet Inc. (NASDAQ: GOOGL) has experienced a significant surge in its stock price, rising nearly 5% to $286 and marking a 63% rally over the last four months, its strongest performance since its 2004 IPO. This increase follows a strong third-quarter report, with analysts at Goldman Sachs and Bank of America raising their price targets for the company. Goldman Sachs raised its 12-month price target to $330, a 15% upside from current levels, citing Alphabet's strong position in AI-powered consumer and enterprise computing. Bank of America raised its price target to $335, implying a 17% upside. Analysts believe Alphabet's AI momentum is accelerating and that there is still room for growth in the stock price.
